  "body": "Currently, adding or removing request/response headers is hard-coded to the following order [0]:\r\n\r\n* route specific\r\n* vhost specific\r\n* connection manager level\r\n\r\nThis means that you can't set global configs (e.g.: vhost or conn manager level) and then unset them at the route specific level.\r\n\r\nWould it be acceptable to have a  config option -- say `reverse_header_evaluation_order` -- to support the reverse order (from least to most specific: conn manager -> vhost -> route)?\r\n\r\nOr would this break anything else?\r\n\r\ncc: @mattklein123 \r\n\r\n[0] https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/source/common/router/config_impl.cc#L386",
